                  <item xml:id="e1"><desc>Attempts to erase lines of text on <locus target="#51r #78r #113r #136v" facs="051 078 113 137">fols. 51r, 78r, 113r, 136v</locus></desc></item>
                  <item xml:id="e2"><desc><locus target="#171v" facs="172">Fol. 171v</locus> blank </desc></item>
                  <item xml:id="e4"><desc>Vellum is in fair condition but showing heavy use.</desc></item>
                  <item xml:id="e5"><desc>The codex has been trimmed since its original production.  Most of the prickings are missing from the fore edge. On several folios, some text is trimmed. The upper margin is abnormally small; the lower margin is also.</desc></item>
                  <item xml:id="e6">
                    <locus target="#4r #17r #25r #27v" facs="004 017 025 028">Fols. 4r, 17r, 25r, 27v</locus>
                    <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                    </item>
                  <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#25v #40r #76r #95r" facs="026 040 076 095">Fols. 25v, 40r, 76r, 95r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., and lines of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#53r" facs="053">f. 53r, line 20</locus>
                    <desc>lines of text are written interlinearly with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted</desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e9">
                  <locus target="#5v #20r #32r" facs="006 020 032">Fols. 5v, 20r, 32r</locus>)
                  <desc>e.g., text has been removed</desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id="e10"><desc>
                    The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect
                    ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. Where the line of text is too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below
                    the end of the line (throughout)</desc></item>
                  </list></additions>
